      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "Poligon's operational strength lies in its ability to deliver <cite id=\"3\">direct service programs</cite> such as voter engagement and legislative advocacy on a minimal budget. By focusing on <cite id=\"12\">action alerts and policy briefings</cite>, they provide immediate value to their constituency. Their financial health is marked by a <cite id=\"5\">85.0% program ratio</cite>, which is a testament to their commitment to mission-centric spending. This efficiency is paired with a <cite id=\"8\">formal zakat eligibility status</cite>, making them a unique option for donors looking to fund <cite id=\"9\">civic education within an Islamic framework</cite>."
      ],
      "summary": "The Poligon Education Fund is a specialized non-profit organization dedicated to <cite id=\"1\">increasing civic engagement through educational resources</cite> and congressional advocacy training. Founded in <cite id=\"2\">2017</cite>, the organization addresses a critical gap in the American Muslim community by providing the tools necessary for effective legislative participation. Their core programming includes <cite id=\"3\">Congressional Advocacy Trainings, Action Alerts, and Policy Briefings</cite>, which aim to demystify the federal legislative process for constituents. Despite its relatively small scale, with <cite id=\"4\">total revenue of $32,150</cite> in the most recent fiscal year, the organization maintains a lean operational model. Financial records indicate a <cite id=\"5\">program expense ratio of 85.0%</cite>, suggesting that nearly all funding is directed toward its educational and advocacy missions. Furthermore, Poligon has demonstrated <cite id=\"6\">exceptional fundraising efficiency</cite>, spending only <cite id=\"7\">$0.23 to raise every $1</cite> in contributions. The organization is also <cite id=\"8\">verified as zakat-eligible</cite>, specifically under the category of <cite id=\"9\">fisabilillah</cite>, allowing Muslim donors to support civic empowerment as a form of religious obligation.",
